problem:
Find all values of the parameters \(a, b, c\) for which the system of equations
\[
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
a x + b y = c \\
b x + c y = a \\
c x + a y = b
\end{array}
\right\}
\]
has at least one negative solution (where \(x, y < 0\)).

A $3 \times 3 \times 3$ cube is made out of $1 \times 1 \times 1$ smaller cubes. What is the maximum number of smaller cubes that can be removed while ensuring that the remaining structure satisfies the following two properties:

- Looking at any face of the original cube, the structure appears as a $3 \times 3$ square (there are no gaps, and all 9 cubes on each face are visible when looking perpendicularly at that face);
- It is possible to travel from any cube to any other cube within the structure by moving through the shared faces of adjacent cubes.

Solve the system of equations:
\[
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
x + y = 13 \\
\log_{4} x + \log_{4} y = 1 + \log_{4} 10
\end{array}
\right.
\]

Given the definitions of sets I, M, N, and P, and the four statements regarding these sets:

(1) M ∪ N ∪ P = I;
(2) N ≠ ∅;
(3) M ≠ ∅;
(4) P ≠ ∅.

Determine the number of correct statements. Express your answer as a single integer.

Find the number of ordered triples $(x,y,z)$ of real numbers that satisfy
\begin{align*}
x + y - z &= 0, \\
xz - xy + yz &= 27, \\
xyz &= 54.
\end{align*}

Given the following pseudo-code:
```
a=3; 
b=-5; 
c=8; 
a=b; 
b=c; 
c=a; 
```
What is the output of the print statement `Print(“%d %d %d”, a, b, c)`? Express your answer as three integer values separated by commas.
